&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;Vectra® is the leader in AI-driven threat detection and response for hybrid and multi-cloud enterprises.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;p1&quot;&gt;The Vectra AI Platform delivers integrated signal across public cloud, SaaS, identity, and data center networks in a single platform. Powered by patented Attack Signal Intelligence, it empowers security teams to rapidly prioritize, investigate and respond to the most advanced cyber-attacks. With 35 patents in AI-driven threat detection and the most vendor references in MITRE D3FEND, organizations worldwide rely on the Vectra AI to move at the speed and scale of hybrid attackers. For more information, visit www.vectra.ai.&lt;span class=&quot;Apple-converted-space&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Commissions Analyst&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Role Summary&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Commissions Analyst is responsible for supporting the administration, calculation, validation, and reporting of sales commission payments. This role partners closely with Sales, Finance, Payroll, HR, and Revenue Operations to ensure commission calculations are accurate, timely, compliant with compensation plans, and clearly communicated to stakeholders.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Calculate, validate, and process commission payments in accordance with approved sales compensation plans and payout schedules.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Review commissionable transactions, bookings, revenue, quota attainment, credits, adjustments, and exceptions to ensure accurate payouts.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Research and resolve commission inquiries, disputes, and statement questions from sales representatives and sales leadership.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with Sales Operations, Revenue Operations, Finance, Payroll, HR, and Accounting to reconcile data and support timely commission processing.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain commission data, plan documents, participant eligibility, territory assignments, quota information, and crediting rules.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prepare monthly and quarterly commission reporting, variance analysis, accrual support, and payout summaries for business stakeholders.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform audits and quality checks to ensure data integrity, policy compliance, and adherence to internal controls.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support compensation plan implementation, system testing, process documentation, and annual plan rollout activities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify opportunities to improve commission processes, reporting accuracy, automation, and stakeholder experience.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Handle confidential compensation information with discretion and professionalism.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
